summary: This document appears to be a communication from AT&T regarding the inability to obtain location information for a specific mobile number. It outlines potential reasons for the lack of data and provides a cautionary note about the reliability of the location data sourced from various databases.
keyFacts: The document indicates that location information could not be obtained due to the mobile being powered off, out of service area, or in an area where location information is unavailable.
The case ID is referenced but redacted, indicating it is part of an ongoing investigation.
The mobile number is partially redacted, showing only the last four digits.
The document emphasizes caution in using the location data for investigative purposes due to potential inaccuracies.
The date of the document is June 30, 2020.
